div.p:
In the campaigning thus far, the Left has taken and is holding an initiative in
                    most of the issues. It may be expected that as the campaign progresses, these
                    issues will, in general terms, be: 
                        (1)

National independence;
                        (2)

the essentially economic and social “problem of the South”;
                        (3)

the politico-economic “class struggle”;
                        (4)

the Catholic Church;
                        (5)

good old-fashioned mud slinging;
                        (6)

the maintenance of peace and order in the country.
